he wrote the music?

00:08:34.630 --> 00:08:36.710
He played the music.

00:08:36.710 --> 00:08:41.080
Do know that he wrote
most of the scripts?

00:08:41.080 --> 00:08:46.820
Do you know that he had advanced
degrees in child development?

00:08:46.820 --> 00:08:50.480
So it didn't just come
from his imagination.

00:08:50.480 --> 00:08:53.960
It came from his heart, and
his soul, and his training.

00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:57.810
So there's so much
embedded in the stories

00:08:57.810 --> 00:09:02.060
that he told, way beyond.

00:09:02.060 --> 00:09:04.455
He was not a typical performer.

00:09:04.455 --> 00:09:05.830
He wasn't an actor.

00:09:05.830 --> 00:09:07.850
In fact, David
will share with you

00:09:07.850 --> 00:09:10.420
some of the stories
about how reluctant he

00:09:10.420 --> 00:09:14.850
was to do things other than
keep building a great show.

00:09:14.850 --> 00:09:19.500
So the show went
on the air in '67?

00:09:19.500 --> 00:09:24.490
DAVID NEWELL: It went on
air February 18, 1968.

00:09:24.490 --> 00:09:27.270
We started taping in '67.

00:09:27.270 --> 00:09:30.810
DONNA MITROFF: So on the
air five times a week,

00:09:30.810 --> 00:09:35.900
every week, for an
entire 35 years.

00:09:35.900 --> 00:09:41.530
So there's a lot of Mr.
Rogers embedded in your minds.

00:09:41.530 --> 00:09:42.650
And its back there.

00:09:42.650 --> 00:09:44.660
And what we're
going to do is help

00:09:44.660 --> 00:09:49.036
you bring those lessons
back forward to today.

00:09:49.036 --> 00:09:50.660
IAN MITROFF: Let me
just add one thing.

00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:54.060
Probably most people don't
know that Fred was an ordained

00:09:54.060 --> 00:09:55.860
Presbyterian minister.

00:09:55.860 --> 00:09:58.890
And he looked at the state
of children's television

00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:01.350
as it was at the time--
mostly like throwing pies

00:10:01.350 --> 00:10:05.490
in people's faces-- and
his ministry literally

00:10:05.490 --> 00:10:09.010
became to make
television for children

00:10:09.010 --> 00:10:11.640
what it should and must become.

00:10:11.640 --> 00:10:14.350
And that really was
this lifelong goal.

00:10:16.980 --> 00:10:20.690
DONNA MITROFF: Now,
his major show was "Mr.

00:10:20.690 --> 00:10:24.130
Rogers' Neighborhood." and
"Mr. Rogers' Neighborhood"

00:10:24.130 --> 00:10:26.760
was made up of these
two different segments.

00:10:26.760 --> 00:10:29.320
You remember how he would
come in, put on his sweater,

00:10:29.320 --> 00:10:30.890
change his shoes.

00:10:30.890 --> 00:10:32.830
He did that because
kids like routine.

00:10:32.830 --> 00:10:36.250
It gets to be very
comfortable for you.

00:10:36.250 --> 00:10:41.310
But then he would go into
his own home, on the set,

00:10:41.310 --> 00:10:43.700
and there would be
many experiences where

00:10:43.700 --> 00:10:46.310
he would bring people
in and they would talk.

00:10:46.310 --> 00:10:48.940
He would take you
out to visit places

00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:52.012
that people love, like the
visit to the Crayon Factory.

00:10:52.012 --> 00:10:52.970
Kids play with crayons.

00:10:52.970 --> 00:10:55.670
They want to know how
do crayons get made?

00:10:55.670 --> 00:10:58.610
So he would take
people to real places

00:10:58.610 --> 00:11:03.070
and do documentary
footage in a real setting.

00:11:03.070 --> 00:11:05.970
And one of the
highlights of his show

00:11:05.970 --> 00:11:09.040
was always the Neighborhood
of Make Believe.

00:11:09.040 --> 00:11:11.780
He'd send that little
trolley around the track.

00:11:11.780 --> 00:11:13.680
And this was done
very deliberately.

00:11:13.680 --> 00:11:15.830
So you're leaving
the real world,

00:11:15.830 --> 00:11:17.710
and you're going
into a neighborhood

00:11:17.710 --> 00:11:20.230
of make believe where
anything can happen.

00:11:20.230 --> 00:11:22.230
And the Neighborhood
of Make Believe

00:11:22.230 --> 00:11:27.450
was populated by puppets
that everyone came to know.

00:11:27.450 --> 00:11:31.020
Here's just a few of them King
Friday, Queen Sarah Saturday,

00:11:31.020 --> 00:11:34.620
Lady Elaine Fairchilde, Lady
Aberlin, and Daniel Tiger.

00:11:34.620 --> 00:11:39.700
Daniel tiger, the one who is
now the star of the new show.

00:11:39.700 --> 00:11:42.360
Many others in the
Neighborhood of Make Believe,

00:11:42.360 --> 00:11:45.600
and some live
performers, never Fred.

00:11:45.600 --> 00:11:47.930
You never saw him in the
Neighborhood of Make Believe

00:11:47.930 --> 00:11:49.330
because he was real.

00:11:49.330 --> 00:11:53.400
But you saw some of the other
people as live performers.

00:11:53.400 --> 00:11:54.350
David was there.

00:11:54.350 --> 00:11:58.160
You would see David in the
Neighborhood of Make Believe.

00:11:58.160 --> 00:12:02.280
And in that Neighborhood
of Make Believe

00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:09.400
is where we found this richness
of information and ideas

00:12:09.400 --> 00:12:10.840
that we want to share with you.

