00:30:18.650 --> 00:30:21.840
There's an error that is
virtually never talked about,

00:30:21.840 --> 00:30:23.080
which is most fundamental.

00:30:23.080 --> 00:30:24.630
It's the type three error.

00:30:24.630 --> 00:30:27.876
The type three error is solving
the wrong problem precisely.

00:30:27.876 --> 00:30:29.500
I'm sure you can all
connect with that.

00:30:29.500 --> 00:30:32.460
Solving the wrong
problem precisely.

00:30:32.460 --> 00:30:35.620
To know that we're not solving
the wrong problem precisely,

00:30:35.620 --> 00:30:39.070
what we have to do is have
at least two different ways

00:30:39.070 --> 00:30:40.090
of looking at a problem.

00:30:40.090 --> 00:30:42.000
If you have only
one alternative,

00:30:42.000 --> 00:30:43.800
that's really a
set up that you're

00:30:43.800 --> 00:30:45.230
going to solve
the wrong problem.

00:30:45.230 --> 00:30:47.420
And that's really what
the fable is about.

00:30:47.420 --> 00:30:49.720
And that's what we
